But important caveat: it didn't consider fed regs requiring passengers to #MaskUp. We know high-filtration masks are very protective. https://t.co/PwfJzSz36y https://t.co/HEUJKVK3H7

Remember no #vaccine is 100% effective & there are now ~77 mil fully #vaccinated US adults. While there may be additional mild & asymptomatic cases that haven't been detected, remember the trials measured symptomatic #Covid: reducing disease severity was largely the point. (2/3)

@CDCgov is tracking breakthrough cases - people developing #Covid after being fully #vaccinated. So far, they've counted ~5,800 cases of which ~400 were hospitalized and 74 died. But here is why this isn't surprising (1/3) https://t.co/Qd5Jzhi4k0

Vaccine advisers to the CDC ended their emergency meeting today without a vote on J&J’s Covid-19 vaccine, while the rollout remains on pause in the US. They want more info on a handful of cases of rare blood clots and plan to meet again within the next week and a half. (1/3)

The US is now administering more than 3 mil #COVID19Vaccine/day. How did we do it? Claire Hannan of the Association of Immunization Managers tells me it's not one size fits all when it comes to #vaccine strategy & what we need to be prepared for in the next phase of the rollout. https://t.co/G9lYankFBc

We filmed this documentary before the Covid pandemic because vaccine hesitancy is not new. Even today, it remains around 20% in this country. If that hesitancy doesn't decrease, we will have a hard time reaching herd immunity by vaccinating adults alone. (1/2)
Thanks @DavidFajgenbaum. A fascinating conversation about how to go about identifying good (often cheap) candidates for “repurposed” drugs — to treat COVID. https://t.co/eB8Co2Fp8r

We’re making great progress on vaccination, but more so in older age groups that are more vulnerable, versus younger folks who are driving the spread of Covid-19 and its more contagious variants. (2/2) https://t.co/eo9ERfmudd
Dr. Fauci told CNN that Covid-19 cases have plateaued at a disturbingly high level. That’s around where we were during last summer’s peak. Today’s “low” is yesterday’s high. (1/2)

As you think about a hopefully more normal summer and school year next fall, please try and be mindful of the growing number of Covid orphans. A new model estimates nearly 40,000 children have lost a parent to this disease. Hug them tight, and #BeKind 
https://t.co/YQxLtrXz1x
